Great! The derive macro automatically creates a field for each subcommand. Here’s a minimal example:

#[derive(Parser, Debug)]
struct Cli {
    #[clap(subcommand, description = "List files", value_parser = "<paths>")]
    List { paths } = Commands::List,
}

impl Commands {
    pub enum List {
        Get(String),
    }
}

When you run `cargo exec --bin my_cli list -p a.txt b.txt`, it will output colored info and return exit 0 on success. It also works with tab completion because clap’s TabComplete trait is implemented.
